# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# .env.local is gitignored and never committed.
#
# UDCPINE_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN
#   Sets a stable, reusable bootstrap token for the backend's pairing URL.
#   When this is set, the printed "Pair a device" URL stays the same across
#   server restarts — a requirement for the Pi kiosk, which is hard-coded to
#   a single URL at deploy time (see plans/ops/2026-05-27-pi-boot-to-kiosk.md).
#
#   Without this var, a fresh random token is generated on every server start,
#   which means the kiosk URL changes on every `make serve` and the Pi can no
#   longer auto-pair after a laptop reboot.
#
#   Generate a token:
#     openssl rand -hex 32
#
# UDCPINE_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN=your-stable-token-here
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Sheets export (optional)
#
# When BOTH of the following are set, each completed firing
# (POST /api/firing/stop) is pushed to a Google Sheet: a summary row on a
# "Firings" tab, a row per pizza on a "Pizzas" tab, and a "firing-<id>" tab with
# the full temperature series. Leave either unset and export is disabled (no-op)
# — dev, CI, and a Pi without credentials all behave exactly as before.
#
# Auth is OAuth (installed-app / "Desktop" flow), not a service-account key
# (the org policy iam.disableServiceAccountKeyCreation blocks key downloads).
# Mint authorized_user.json ONCE on a laptop, then copy it to the Pi:
#     uv run python scripts/sheets_oauth_bootstrap.py \
#         --client-secret /path/to/client_secret.json --out authorized_user.json
# See plans/backend/2026-06-16-google-sheets-export.md for the full setup.
#
# UDCPINE_SHEETS_OAUTH_TOKEN
#   Path to the minted authorized_user.json (chmod 600; never commit it).
# UDCPINE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID
#   The spreadsheet id from its URL: .../spreadsheets/d/<ID>/edit
#
# UDCPINE_SHEETS_OAUTH_TOKEN=authorized_user.json
# UDCPINE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID=your-spreadsheet-id-here
